The paper discusses statistical methods for auditing election results, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Bayesian methods and the mention of ranked-choice voting suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves statistical analysis and sampling, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
